      "content": "i feel like calling it a \"consensus\" kind of brushes over the actual debate though. like, what about the people who argue that the movement's focus on nonviolence actually slowed down real progress, or that the legislative wins were just surface level changes that didn't address the core issues? isn't there more of a conflict there than just \"it worked vs it was incomplete\"??",
